<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4960/77.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Yenikeny</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-15"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>No. 48. Beferring to the fifth demand in his telegram of April 10,
                            reports the satisfactory settlement of the Manoukian case,<note n="a" xml:id="d415fna">See following subject.</note> which has been so
                            long pending, and which involved the recognition by the Sublime Porte of
                            our consular courts as alone competent to decide as to legal heirs of an
                            American citizen.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>